portant; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1659008080557" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1659008080557"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><font color="#000000">1. Purpose</font></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1698608123247" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1698608123247"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Weightlifting belts are engineered to <a href="https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/Effects-of-a-belt-on-intra-abdominal-pressure-Harman-Rosenstein/f23b4cc1cf7b90e1715509a0b47529447e814490" class="" target="_blank">increase intra-abdominal pressure</a> and thus <a href="https://www.researchgate.net/publication/232184433" class="" target="_blank">provide additional support to the spine</a> during heavier lifts. So long story short — increasing performance and <a href="https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/An-evaluation-of-a-weightlifting-belt-and-back-for-Reddell-Congleton/343828324e5a07c713e5125ba41b307e8ab1c909" class="" target="_blank">minimizing the chance to sustain injury</a>. A 3-inch belt is an amazing choice because it offers enough support without being too bulky or restrictive.</p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p></div></div><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1660105003750" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1660105003750" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-exc=""><a href="Lifting Belt in Use by Female" target=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/0fd3b6c4-3ad2-4c6d-b636-c89d8f618489/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/Using-Belt-by-Female.jpg" alt="Lifting Belt in Use" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="1200" height="800" data-width="100%" data-height="auto" title="Lifting Belt in Use by Female" natural-width="1200" natural-height="800"></a></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1698608232637" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1698608232637"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><font color="#000000">2. Material</font></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1698608236541" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1698608236541"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">The most popular materials used for lifting belts are leather and synthetic materials like nylon. Leather is usually more expensive, and <a href="https://lifehacker.com/when-weightlifting-belts-are-necessary-and-when-theyre-1766557417" class="" target="_blank">offers more support</a>, but these belts are also usually not as comfortable as their synthetic brethren. When deciding on the material, also think of material quality. Getting better quality materials is usually a surefire <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC9282110/" class="" target="_blank">way of squeezing out more performance</a> and ensuring higher product longevity.</p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1698608286385" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1698608286385"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><font color="#000000">3. Thickness & Width</font></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1698608287929" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1698608287929"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Thickness and width will determine how much support a lifting belt will provide. The 10mm thickness (usually accompanied by a +/- 1 mm margin of error) is standard for most belts. And it strikes a good balance between support and comfort. The 3’’ width is preferable for lifters with a shorter torso, or for athletes that require a greater degree of flexibility, for example, Olympic lifters.</p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1698608299338" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1698608299338"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><font color="#000000">4. Closure system</font></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1698608300725" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1698608300725"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">For closure, you’ll usually find a prong buckle on leather belts or a Velcro system on a nylon belt. On others, you can also find a lever. If you are looking for ease of use, then lean towards levers. Buckles (such as you have on a lot of leather belts) tend to be more adjustable but are also much trickier or more annoying to use. Velcro strikes a good balance between adjustability and fastening swiftness but is usually lacking the support or longevity that you get with a lever or a buckle system.</p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1698606451600" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1698606451600"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">3 vs 4 Inch Lifting Belts&nbsp;</h2></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1698606506927" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1698606506927"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Both 3 and 4-inch lifting belts are popular sizes to use when lifting. The belt width that's right for you depends on your build, hip width, and what you need the belt for. The 1-inch size difference offers different pros and cons for lifters and makes the sizes suitable for different uses. So what are the pros and cons of each and should you choose a 3 or 4-inch powerlifting belt?</p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p></div></div><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1659326706667" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1659326706667" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/8f1afd73-3744-4220-8138-f710d806bb65/-/format