wrap" data-id="1698606946080"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-exc=""><p style="text-align: inherit!important;">Less flexibility offered and may dig into torso</p></div></div></div></li><li style="margin-bottom: 15px"><span class="gf-il-icon item-content" data-index="3" data-key="content" style="width: 45px"><div data-label="Icon" id="e-1698606982077" class="element-wrap" data-id="1698606982077" data-icon="gpicon-icon" data-ver="1.0"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf-elm-center-lg gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs" data-exc=""><div class="gf_icon-wrap" style="font-size: 20px; color: rgb(221, 51, 51);"><i class="gf_icon fa fa-close"></i></div></div></div></span><div class="gf-il-content item-content" data-index="3" data-key="content1" style="padding-left: 45px"><div data-label="Text Block" id="e-1698606982138" class="element-wrap" data-id="1698606982138"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-exc=""><p style="text-align: inherit!important;">May not be suitable for smaller lifters</p></div></div></div></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1660101673019" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1660101673019"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Who Needs a 4 Inch Lifting Belt?</span></h3></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1661924746056" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1661924746056"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h4 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><strong>1. Larger Individuals&nbsp;</strong></h4></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1660101680601" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1660101680601" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p><span style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px;">Due to the size of your torso, if you're a larger individual you will benefit more from the 4-inch belt option.&nbsp;</span><br></p><p>You want the belt to sit tight against your back and core, but not so tight that it limits movement and makes lifting uncomfortable. If you're a larger individual, a 3-inch belt may not be suitable for your torso and take the focus away from natural bracing and performing the movement correctly.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1698609469018" class="gf_row gf_row-gap-0" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1698609469018" data-row-gap="0px" data-extraclass=""><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-12 gf_col-md-12 gf_col-sm-12 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1686320640542" data-id="1686320640542"><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1698609468976" class="gf_row gf_row-gap-0" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1698609468976" data-layout-lg="6+6" data-extraclass="" data-layout-md="6+6" data-layout-sm="6+6" data-layout-xs="8+4" data-row-gap="0px"><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-6 gf_col-md-6 gf_col-sm-6 gf_col-xs-8" id="c-1686566620521" data-id="1686566620521"><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1698609468933" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1698609468933"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><b>Tips From the Champ</b></h2></div></div></div><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-6 gf_col-md-6 gf_col-sm-6 gf_col-xs-4" id="c-1686566621695" data-id="1686566621695"><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1698609469026" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1698609469026" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-right-lg gf-elm-right-md gf-elm-right-sm gf-elm-right-xs" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/d583efb1-a2f6-4d53-8a26-d6ddafaa60fd/7350738.png" alt="" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="512" height="512" data-width="50%" data-height="auto" title="" natural-width="512" natural-height="512"></div></div></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1698609468981" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1698609468981"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc="">When in the market for a 10mm 3-inch weightlifting belt, it’s best to check the leather quality, as this will determine how much stability the belt provides. Opt for high-quality leather. Also, consider sizing options, as a wide range of options will save you from having to compromise on a fit that doesn’t suit you perfectly. A tight and easy adjustable buckle will help with mid-set adjustments, if necessary, and will also help keep your midsection stable during heavy lifts. A longer warranty (3 years to a lifetime) will help with brand trust and peace of mind.</div></div><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1698609469009" class="gf_row gf_row-gap-0" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1698609469009" data-layout-lg="6+6" data-extraclass="" data-layout-md="6+6" data-layout-sm="6+6" data-layout-xs="12+12" data-row-gap=